defaultTo compare
default like-for-like authorities, if you look at unitary authorities, in 2014-2015, the difference is about 10%; if you look at the shire district areas, in 2014-2015 it will be 12%; if you look at fire and rescue authorities, it will be about minus 3%; and for county councils, it will be about 4%.  That is because the way they assess what is a rural area is quite different 
defaultfrom 
defaultthe way we do.  In a simplistic sense—I can give you a colloquial example of this—the way they look at the rural definition, they would include 
defaultNorfolk
